Interface IPlcioPcFormatType


  • public interface IPlcioPcFormatType
    Interface describing PLCIO pcFormat strings as represented by objects of type PlcioPcFormatType.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getTypeId

        char getTypeId()
        Get the typeId describing the type of this type descriptor of the pcFormat string.

        E.g. if the type of this type descriptor is int the typeId will be j.

        Returns:
        the typeId

      • getByteLen

        int getByteLen()
        Get the byte length used to store all data described by this type.
        Returns:
        byte length used to store all data described by this type.

      • getNumberOfMembers

        int getNumberOfMembers()
        Get the number of members.

        E.g. if the typeId is j (int), and byteLen is 8, then number of members will be 2 (total byte length divided by byte length of type int (4)).

        Returns:
        number of members.

      • getTypeIdStr

        java.lang.String getTypeIdStr()
        Get a String representation of the type.

        E.g. if the typeID is j the typeIdStr will be int.

        Returns:
        String representation of the type.
